{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17566769","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17566769"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:47:53+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:47:53+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18875"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18875","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18875"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.02,0.61,0.28,0.01,0.08]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11608"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114348"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11608","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11608"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18875"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96348"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"10"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"27"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"2436"},{"type":"tags","id":"2982"},{"type":"tags","id":"4958"},{"type":"tags","id":"4989"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11323"},{"type":"tags","id":"11327"},{"type":"tags","id":"11328"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27316"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27318"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44742"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45083"},{"type":"contributions","id":"47518"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114348","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/114348"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA junior doctor has been working in a busy Emergency Department for six months. They have recently started making more clinical errors and frequently arrive late to work. They express cynical attitudes towards patients and colleagues. They report feeling constantly tired despite adequate sleep and have lost interest in previously enjoyable activities both at work and home.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the combination of features most consistent with professional burnout?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Anxiety, perfectionism and social withdrawal","Emotional exhaustion, depersonalisation and reduced sense of accomplishment","Depression, fatigue and poor concentration","Self-doubt, fear of failure and procrastination","Reduced empathy, hypervigilance and irritability"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEmotional exhaustion, depersonalisation and reduced accomplishment\u003C/strong\u003E represents the complete triad of professional burnout. This combination uniquely characterises burnout syndrome, distinguishing it from other psychological conditions.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAnxiety, perfectionism and social withdrawal\u003C/strong\u003E - While these may occur in burnout, this combination better describes generalised anxiety disorder\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDepression, fatigue and poor concentration\u003C/strong\u003E - These symptoms overlap with burnout but are more characteristic of clinical depression\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESelf-doubt, fear of failure and procrastination\u003C/strong\u003E - This combination better describes imposter syndrome\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReduced empathy, hypervigilance and irritability\u003C/strong\u003E - These features better align with compassion fatigue or secondary traumatic stress\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe presence of all three cardinal features is required for a complete picture of professional burnout:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Col\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEmotional exhaustion i.e., feeling depleted\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDepersonalisation i.e., cynical attitudes\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EReduced sense of accomplishment i.e., feeling of inadequacy regarding clinical duties.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ol\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Professional burnout is characterized by three key components: emotional exhaustion, depersonalization, and reduced personal accomplishment.","Burnout manifests through both psychological symptoms (cynicism, detachment) and physical symptoms (fatigue, sleep disturbance).","Burnout differs from other psychological conditions by its specific work-related context and combination of symptoms."],"references":["Nadon L, De Beer LT, Morin AJS. Should Burnout Be Conceptualized as a Mental Disorder? Behav Sci (Basel). 2022 Mar 17;12(3):82. Available at: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC8945132/#sec3-behavsci-12-00082","Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96348"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18875"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96348","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/96348"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-15T18:57:50+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-15T18:58:21+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11608"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"que